sl7Hxdhm0X7rWBaoA28t9d3r4H9BBQ972wK1T75miNIbfpkgFLrTML9hlW8PEu5n20l5XdS3z_4AaOgEZ6uB1KC38BDBx4gkRcpy0KrPJmj9RlGZKF5Oga_Cw5MP8U_K2gyjyXb7IPnaan0cuOXE7NJ5D3oH6jod8poHkXbvoBE=\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering GraalVM native image toolchain**\\n\\nI'm exploring whether the GraalVM native image plugin uses a toolchain. It seems like it may need to enforce a Java 21 compiler for tests, but the native image might rely on the installed GraalVM. I'm wondering if it requires the native-image from version 21 as well. But I think this topic is getting very broad and version-specific, since it might hardcode the Java version instead of just the library artifact.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Addressing Java security issues**\\n\\nI’m considering calling hashcode or toString, which seems good. However, there might be a potential issue if tests run on JDK21 with `-Djava.security.manager=default`. If the first test clears the security manager, I wonder if Java prohibits re-enabling it afterward? This could complicate things further, and I want to ensure I'm understanding the implications around Java's security features properly. I might need to explore this issue more closely.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering Gradle's Test class**\\n\\nI’m looking into whether Gradle's default imports include the `org.gradle.api.tasks.testing.Test` class. Many build scripts use `tasks.withType(Test)`, which is pretty common. I’m thinking it might be helpful to add comments in the code, but I'm also considering that it isn't strictly necessary. Oh, and I need to remember that we won’t be compiling or running tests. Keeping that in mind as I proceed!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_agQZT0SjrS973KOlURUDvVBq|fc_0c090013604f2c400169fc50591810819f94b8c6f454da0567", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/jakarta.enterprise/jakarta.enterprise.cdi-api/3.0.0/src/test/resources/all-permissions.policy"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 537, "output": 2112, "cacheRead": 29696, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 32345, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778143289038, "responseId": "resp_0c090013604f2c400169fc5039dab4819fb5c959a201b8a30f"}}
